
# Trello

![Tech Stack](https://img.shields.io/badge/Tech%20Stack-React%20%7C%20TailwindCSS%20%7C%20Redux%20Toolkit%20%7C%20React%20Router%20%7C%20React%20Query-blue)

## 🚀 Project Overview
A professional React-based project set up with modern technologies like Tailwind CSS, Redux Toolkit, React Router, and React Query for efficient state and data management.

## 📌 Features
- 🚀 **React** – Component-based architecture.
- 🎨 **Tailwind CSS** – Utility-first styling for a sleek UI.
- ⚡ **Redux Toolkit** – State management with persistence.
- 🔄 **React Query** – Efficient data fetching and caching.
- 🔗 **React Router** – Seamless client-side routing.
- 🌐 **Axios** – Simplified API requests.
- ✨ **ShadCN** – Pre-built UI components.

## 📂 Folder Structure
```
📦 project-name
├── 📂 src
│   ├── 📂 components  # Ui components
│   ├── 📂 common      # Reusable UI components
│   ├── 📂 services    # api calls
│   ├── 📂 pages       # Route pages
│   ├── 📂 hooks       # Custom hooks
│   ├── 📂 utils       # Helper functions, third-pary libraries
│   ├── 📂 assets      # Static files (images, icons)
│   ├── index.css      # Global styles
│   ├── App.tsx       # Main app entry
│   ├── main.tsx      # React DOM root
│   ├── store.ts      # Redux store
│   └── routes.tsx    # App routing
├── 📜 .gitignore      # Git ignore file
├── 📜 README.md       # Project documentation
├── 📜 package.json    # Dependencies & scripts
└── 📜 tailwind.config.js  # Tailwind setup
```

## 🛠 Installation & Setup
### 1️⃣ Clone the repository
```sh
git clone https://github.com/gtsaroj/trello_prototype.git
cd trello
```

### 2️⃣ Install dependencies
```sh
yarn install  # or npm install
```

### 3️⃣ Run the development server
```sh
yarn dev  # or npm run dev
```

## 🎯 Scripts
| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `npm run dev` | Start development server |
| `npm run build` | Build for production |
| `npm run lint` | Run ESLint checks |
| `npm run format` | Format code with Prettier |

## 🚀 Deployment
You can deploy this app using **Vercel**, **Netlify**, or **Docker**. Example:
```sh
vercel deploy  # Deploy to Vercel
```

